{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "While there is no nationwide policy specifically for STEM education in China, the government has supported innovative teaching methods.",
    "The 2016 Ministry of Education's \"13th Five-Year Plan for Educational Informatization\" promoted fresh educational approaches, including maker spaces and interdisciplinary studies (Ministry of Education of China, 2016).",
    "Following this, regions such as Jiangsu have introduced their own STEM initiatives, with the ambitious \"China STEM Education 2029 Innovation Action Plan\" outlining a decade-long vision tailored to the country's unique educational needs (An et al. 2020).",
    "These regional initiatives are crucial as they allow for localized adaptation of STEM education strategies, ensuring that they meet the specific needs of different areas within China.",
    "However, the variation in implementation across regions underscores the importance of understanding how these localized efforts align with broader educational goals and the theoretical frameworks that support them."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "The 2016 Ministry of Education's \"13th Five-Year Plan for Educational Informatization\" promoted fresh educational approaches, including maker spaces and interdisciplinary studies (Ministry of Education of China, 2016).",
